  "body": "While starting the design process of policing service that will keep an eye at the network for finding slashable events. as well as protect his own subscribers (Validators) from creating a slashable event.\r\n\r\nThe way to a full blown policing service is comprised of these steps:\r\nBug fixes:\r\n- [x] grpc proto api #3134\r\n- [x] separate db for slasher #3270 \r\n- [x] making slasher grpc server #3271 \r\n- [x] Store historical block headers in local db #3270\r\n- [x] Store indexed attestations in db #3322 / #3897 \r\n- [x] Store min max span per validator #3941\r\n- [x] Update min max span per validator #3951\r\n- [x] Detect surround attestations using min max span #3967\r\n- [x] Proposer slashing detection (db keys)\r\n- [x] Double Attestation detection (db keys) \r\n- [x] Surround attestation detection ([min max span](https://github.com/protolambda/eth2-surround))\r\n- [x] Benchmark surround attestation detection\r\n- [x] Slasher grpc client of beacon node\r\n- [ ] Store active validator state per epoch\r\n- [ ] Store validator index to public key map \r\n- [ ] Validate attestation signature (@rauljordan @0xKiwi  they are verified before being put in pull)\r\n- [ ] Purge attestations and historic block headers bucket to max size #3270\r\n\r\n- [ ] Beacon server detection of all slashable events of its subscribed validators(bitmap 54000 epoches X number of running validators). By storing all the data concerning them in db and validating against it. Panic in case a rpc call is going to create a slashable event. \r\n- [ ] Slasher server with pruning at weak subjectivity period \r\n- [ ] Beacon node / Slasher communication. to feed slasher with attestations and block proposals.\r\n- [ ] Beacon node / Slasher communication. to listen slashable events\r\n- [ ] Slashing simulator\r\n",
